theorem Topology.interior_frontier_interior_compl_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior A ∪ frontier A ∪ interior (Aᶜ) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- It is enough to show that every point belongs to the left-hand side.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    simp at hx
  · intro x _hx
    by_cases hIntA : x ∈ interior A
    · -- `x ∈ interior A`
      exact Or.inl (Or.inl hIntA)
    · by_cases hIntAc : x ∈ interior (Aᶜ)
      · -- `x ∈ interior (Aᶜ)`
        exact Or.inr hIntAc
      · -- `x` belongs to neither interior; it must be in the frontier.
        -- First, show `x ∈ closure A`.
        have hx_closureA : x ∈ closure A := by
          -- If `x ∉ closure A`, then `x ∈ (closure A)ᶜ`, an open set
          -- contained in `Aᶜ`, contradicting `hIntAc`.
          by_contra h
          have hx_open : x ∈ (closure A)ᶜ := by
            simpa using h
          have h_open : IsOpen ((closure A)ᶜ) := isClosed_closure.isOpen_compl
          have h_subset : (closure A)ᶜ ⊆ Aᶜ := by
            intro y hy
            by_contra hyA
            have : y ∈ closure A := subset_closure hyA
            have : y ∈ (closure A)ᶜ := hy
            exact this.elim
          have : x ∈ interior (Aᶜ) :=
            interior_maximal h_subset h_open hx_open
          exact hIntAc this
        -- Assemble frontier membership.
        have hx_frontier : x ∈ frontier A := by
          -- `frontier A = closure A \ interior A`
          exact And.intro hx_closureA hIntA
        exact Or.inl (Or.inr hx_frontier)
